<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-41-1068 </DOCNO><TEXT>Discusses the reduction of NO/sub x/ emission in coal firing, and thedesign of low NO/sub x/ burners using internal combustion air staging.Characterisation of the chemical environment in the vicinity of the aerodynamicallyair staged pulverised coal burner was obtained by detailed in-flame measurementsof low and high NO/sub x/ flames, and provided insight into the mechanismof NO/sub x/ formation and reduction with coal firing. 8 refs.</TEXT></DOC>